President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Edmund G. LaCour, Jr. for the position of Judge on the United States District Court for the Middle District of Alabama. LaCour currently serves as the Solicitor General for the State of Alabama and has previous experience as a Partner in the Washington, D.C. office of Kirkland & Ellis, LLP. He has represented clients before various courts, including the Supreme Court, courts of appeals, and trial courts. LaCour has also practiced at Bancroft PLLC and Baker Botts, LLP. He holds a B.A. from Birmingham-Southern College, an M.Phil. from Trinity College Dublin, and a J.D. from Yale Law School.